This paper deals with the design and analysis of a key agreement protocol, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Weil/Tate pairing suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The protocol also involves identity-based cryptography, which could place it under the category of cyber security (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper proposes an efficient protocol, which could place it under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE) or software engineering (cs.SE).
